parsed.explanation: The XML required normalization of corrupted German characters (e.g., 'Hauß', 'Bräutigam', 'hinauß', 'jüngsten', 'unseligen', 'Buß', 'länger', 'biß'). Structurally, the content describing the work was improperly split by a premature `</TITLE>` tag, and a second closing `</TITLE>` tag appeared later. These segments were merged into a single coherent `<TITLE>` element encompassing the full description within `<BIBL>`. Additionally, the tag `<YEAR>` was misused around the month 'Septembris' and was removed.
